#   Beagle wiki

Beagle: git-compatible LLM-age source code management system.
Project management docs.

 1. [/meta] page format requirements for each parts, e.g. [/meta/wiki],
      - [wiki format and organization][w]
      - [ticket format][t]
      - [tickets and worktrees workflow][o]
      - [API index files (read before work, update after changes)][i]
      - [ABC (ABstractionless C) codebase conventions][a]
 2. [/wiki] defining concepts and connections within the project, essentials:
      - [AB C][A],
      - [Beagle URIs][U],
      - [StrictMark][S],
      - [Beagle's (HTTP) Verbs][V],
 3. [/todo] tickets, issues, todos, ordered by the topic,
 4. [/blog] the project's blog,
 5. [/html] the generated site: a git submodule (public repo `replicated.live`),
 6. [/beagle] the Beagle codebase per se (AB C)

Publishing: edit sources, run `make` (renders into the `html/` submodule), then
`make publish` — commit+push inside `html/`, then bump the gitlink here.

